  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain the <strong>tofu</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper, then cut into strips</p><p>Add the <strong>tofu strips</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half </strong>the <strong>soy sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>marinated tofu</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1644331457208-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1644331457208-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1644331457208-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1644331457208-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1644331457208-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>cornflour </strong>to a plate with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then add the <strong>marinated tofu </strong>and mix it all together<strong> </strong>until all the tofu is coated<strong> </strong>– this is your<strong> coated tofu</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with matching lid) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated tofu</strong> and cook for 5-6 min, turning occasionally until golden and crisp, then transfer to a plate lined with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper and reserve the pan – this is your <strong>crispy tofu</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1644331453738-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1644331453738-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1644331453738-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1644331453738-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1644331453738-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the tofu is cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Cut the<strong> broccoli</strong> into small florets and cut the stem<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1644331461626-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1644331461626-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1644331461626-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1644331461626-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1644331461626-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>broccoli florets </strong>and <strong>stems </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly charred</p><p>Once slightly charred, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1644331472295-x200.jpg",
