          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1644331490326-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the garlic has softened, reduce the heat to medium</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>and <strong>toasted sesame oil </strong>to the pan</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining cornflour</strong> with 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook, covered, for 5-6 min or until the <strong>broccoli</strong> is tender with a slight bite and the sauce has slightly thickened</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1644331503290-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1644331503290-x400.jpg",
